name: Dallas Stars
summary: The Colorado Avalanche and Dallas Stars faced off in a hard-fought Game 4 of their NHL playoff series, with the Stars emerging victorious. name: Colorado Avalanche
summary: The Colorado Avalanche, after losing Valeri Nichushkin to a six-month suspension, are struggling to keep their playoff run alive. Despite Nathan MacKinnon's extended lead, the team has had a series of setbacks, including a six-month suspension to a key player just hours before a playoff loss. The Dallas Stars have capitalized on the Avalanche's misfortune, winning three games in the series and taking a commanding lead. With defense becoming a priority, the Stars have managed to befuddle the Avalanche, forcing them to re-evaluate their strategy. The future of the Avalanche remains uncertain as they face an uphill battle without Nichushkin.

name: Rudy Giuliani
summary: A series of news articles report on various recent events surrounding Rudy Giuliani. At his 80th birthday party, Giuliani was served with legal papers related to the "fake electors case" in Arizona, prompting chaos among guests. Despite being indicted, Giuliani has not yet been officially served with the Arizona indictment, leading to speculation about his whereabouts. Giuliani's radio show has been canceled due to his continued promotion of false election conspiracy theories. WABC Radio also suspended Giuliani for violating a ban on discussing election claims. A bankruptcy judge expressed frustration with Giuliani's case and dismissed an attempt to challenge a $148 million judgment against him, leading to media outlets dubbing him a "deadbeat." Amidst the legal challenges, Giuliani's bizarre Amazon gift registry for his birthday has also garnered attention, including items like Armani cologne, an electric razor, and ceiling paint.

name: Samuel Alito
summary: Several news articles have reported that Supreme Court Justice Samuel Alito's house in Virginia displayed an upside-down American flag after the January 6th Capitol riot. Justice Alito initially claimed that he was unaware of the flag, but later admitted that his wife had put it up following an argument with a neighbor who had made insulting remarks. The incident has sparked controversy, with some questioning whether it indicates a political bias on the part of Justice Alito. While Alito has defended his wife's actions, the incident has cast a negative light on the Supreme Court, which has already been criticized for its perceived political leanings.
